com.i2group.apollo.model.schema.transport

Class ProhibitedRetrieve

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.model.schema.transport.ProhibitedOperation
      • com.i2group.apollo.model.schema.transport.ProhibitedRetrieve

  • public final class ProhibitedRetrieve
extends ProhibitedOperation
    A ProhibitedOperation that indicates that users cannot see items, property groups, or properties of a particular type when retrieving data.

    When a type has this indicator set in the Schema, data retrieval services must filter data of that type out from any results that they return to the client. This has the effect of rendering the data (of that type) invisible, as if the type had never existed.

    For example, if an item type has the ProhibitedRetrieve indicator, then a client must never receive items of that type. If a property type has the ProhibitedRetrieve indicator, then items must not contain properties of that type when they reach the client.

    Since:
    5.0
